41struct nvkm_udevice {
42 struct nvkm_object object;
43 struct nvkm_device *device;
44};
45
46static int
47nvkm_udevice_info(struct nvkm_udevice *udev, void *data, u32 size)
48{
49 struct nvkm_object *object = &udev->object;
50 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
51 struct nvkm_fb *fb = device->fb;
52 struct nvkm_instmem *imem = device->imem;
53 union {
54 struct nv_device_info_v0 v0;
55 } *args = data;
56 int ret;
57
58 nvif_ioctl(object, "device info size %d\n", size);
59 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
60 nvif_ioctl(object, "device info vers %d\n", args->v0.version);
61 } else
62 return ret;
63
64 switch (device->chipset) {
65 case 0x01a:
66 case 0x01f:
67 case 0x04c:
68 case 0x04e:
69 case 0x063:
70 case 0x067:
71 case 0x068:
72 case 0x0aa:
73 case 0x0ac:
74 case 0x0af:
75 args->v0.platform = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_IGP;
76 break;
77 default:
78 switch (device->type) {
79 case NVKM_DEVICE_PCI:
80 args->v0.platform = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_PCI;
81 break;
82 case NVKM_DEVICE_AGP:
83 args->v0.platform = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_AGP;
84 break;
85 case NVKM_DEVICE_PCIE:
86 args->v0.platform = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_PCIE;
87 break;
88 case NVKM_DEVICE_TEGRA:
89 args->v0.platform = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_SOC;
90 break;
91 default:
92 WARN_ON(1);
93 break;
94 }
95 break;
96 }
97
98 switch (device->card_type) {
99 case NV_04: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_TNT; break;
100 case NV_10:
101 case NV_11: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS; break;
102 case NV_20: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KELVIN; break;
103 case NV_30: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_RANKINE; break;
104 case NV_40: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE; break;
105 case NV_50: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_TESLA; break;
106 case NV_C0: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_FERMI; break;
107 case NV_E0: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KEPLER; break;
108 case GM100: args->v0.family = NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_MAXWELL; break;
109 default:
110 args->v0.family = 0;
111 break;
112 }
113
114 args->v0.chipset = device->chipset;
115 args->v0.revision = device->chiprev;
116 if (fb && fb->ram)
117 args->v0.ram_size = args->v0.ram_user = fb->ram->size;
118 else
119 args->v0.ram_size = args->v0.ram_user = 0;
120 if (imem && args->v0.ram_size > 0)
121 args->v0.ram_user = args->v0.ram_user - imem->reserved;
122
123 strncpy(args->v0.chip, device->chip->name, sizeof(args->v0.chip));
124 strncpy(args->v0.name, device->name, sizeof(args->v0.name));
125 return 0;
126}
127
128static int
129nvkm_udevice_time(struct nvkm_udevice *udev, void *data, u32 size)
130{
131 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
132 union {
133 struct nv_device_time_v0 v0;
134 } *args = data;
135 int ret;
136
137 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
138 args->v0.time = nvkm_timer_read(device->timer);
139 }
140
141 return ret;
142}
143
144static int
145nvkm_udevice_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
146{
147 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(object);
148 switch (mthd) {
149 case NV_DEVICE_V0_INFO:
150 return nvkm_udevice_info(udev, data, size);
151 case NV_DEVICE_V0_TIME:
152 return nvkm_udevice_time(udev, data, size);
153 default:
154 break;
155 }
156 return -EINVAL;
157}

207static int
208#ifdef __NetBSD__
209nvkm_udevice_map(struct nvkm_object *object, bus_space_tag_t *tagp, u64 *addr,
210 u32 *size)
211#else
212nvkm_udevice_map(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 *addr, u32 *size)
213#endif
214{
215 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(object);
216 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
217#ifdef __NetBSD__
218 *tagp = device->func->resource_tag(device, 0);
219#endif
220 *addr = device->func->resource_addr(device, 0);
221 *size = device->func->resource_size(device, 0);
222 return 0;
223}

225static int
226nvkm_udevice_fini(struct nvkm_object *object, bool suspend)
227{
228 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(object);
229 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
230 int ret = 0;
231
232 mutex_lock(&device->mutex);
233 if (!--device->refcount) {
234 ret = nvkm_device_fini(device, suspend);
235 if (ret && suspend) {
236 device->refcount++;
237 goto done;
238 }
239 }
240
241done:
242 mutex_unlock(&device->mutex);
243 return ret;
244}
245
246static int
247nvkm_udevice_init(struct nvkm_object *object)
248{
249 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(object);
250 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
251 int ret = 0;
252
253 mutex_lock(&device->mutex);
254 if (!device->refcount++) {
255 ret = nvkm_device_init(device);
256 if (ret) {
257 device->refcount--;
258 goto done;
259 }
260 }
261
262done:
263 mutex_unlock(&device->mutex);
264 return ret;
265}

267static int
268nvkm_udevice_child_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
269 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
270{
271 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(oclass->parent);
272 const struct nvkm_device_oclass *sclass = oclass->priv;
273 return sclass->ctor(udev->device, oclass, data, size, pobject);
274}
275
276static int
277nvkm_udevice_child_get(struct nvkm_object *object, int index,
278 struct nvkm_oclass *oclass)
279{
280 struct nvkm_udevice *udev = nvkm_udevice(object);
281 struct nvkm_device *device = udev->device;
282 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
283 u64 mask = (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_DMAOBJ) |
284 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO) |
285 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_DISP) |
286 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_PM);
287 const struct nvkm_device_oclass *sclass = NULL;
288 int i;
289
290 for (; mask && !sclass && (i = __ffs64(mask), 1); mask &= ~(1ULL << i)) {
291 if (!(engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, i)) ||
292 !(engine->func->base.sclass))
293 continue;
294 oclass->engine = engine;
295
296 index -= engine->func->base.sclass(oclass, index, &sclass);
297 }
298
299 if (!sclass) {
300 switch (index) {
301 case 0: sclass = &nvkm_control_oclass; break;
302 default:
303 return -EINVAL;
304 }
305 oclass->base = sclass->base;
306 }
307
308 oclass->ctor = nvkm_udevice_child_new;
309 oclass->priv = sclass;
310 return 0;
311}

313static const struct nvkm_object_func
314nvkm_udevice_super = {
315 .init = nvkm_udevice_init,
316 .fini = nvkm_udevice_fini,
317 .mthd = nvkm_udevice_mthd,
318 .map = nvkm_udevice_map,
319 .rd08 = nvkm_udevice_rd08,
320 .rd16 = nvkm_udevice_rd16,
321 .rd32 = nvkm_udevice_rd32,
322 .wr08 = nvkm_udevice_wr08,
323 .wr16 = nvkm_udevice_wr16,
324 .wr32 = nvkm_udevice_wr32,
325 .sclass = nvkm_udevice_child_get,
326};
327
328static const struct nvkm_object_func
329nvkm_udevice = {
330 .init = nvkm_udevice_init,
331 .fini = nvkm_udevice_fini,
332 .mthd = nvkm_udevice_mthd,
333 .sclass = nvkm_udevice_child_get,
334};

336static int
337nvkm_udevice_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
338 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
339{
340 union {
341 struct nv_device_v0 v0;
342 } *args = data;
343 struct nvkm_client *client = oclass->client;
344 struct nvkm_object *parent = &client->object;
345 const struct nvkm_object_func *func;
346 struct nvkm_udevice *udev;
347 int ret;
348
349 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create device size %d\n", size);
350 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
351 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create device v%d device %016"PRIx64"\n",
352 args->v0.version, args->v0.device);
353 } else
354 return ret;
355
356 /* give priviledged clients register access */
357 if (client->super)
358 func = &nvkm_udevice_super;
359 else
360 func = &nvkm_udevice;
361
362 if (!(udev = kzalloc(sizeof(*udev), GFP_KERNEL)))
363 return -ENOMEM;
364 nvkm_object_ctor(func, oclass, &udev->object);
365 *pobject = &udev->object;
366
367 /* find the device that matches what the client requested */
368 if (args->v0.device != ~0)
369 udev->device = nvkm_device_find(args->v0.device);
370 else
371 udev->device = nvkm_device_find(client->device);
372 if (!udev->device)
373 return -ENODEV;
374
375 return 0;
376}
377
378const struct nvkm_sclass
379nvkm_udevice_sclass = {
380 .oclass = NV_DEVICE,
381 .minver = 0,
382 .maxver = 0,
383 .ctor = nvkm_udevice_new,
384};
